    • changeOrder

      public Tour changeOrder​(Tour tour, java.util.List<java.lang.Long> newOrder)
      Rearrange an existing request with a given order

      The new order is a list of identity in type of Long, it should be starting and ending with the ID of the intersection of Depot, and its length has to be the same as the original length of Tour.paths.

      Parameters:
      tour - the original tour
      newOrder - the order of intersections that will be applied
      Returns:
      the object Tour after changing, null if the rules above are not respected.
      See Also:
      Tour

    • verifyNewOrder

      public boolean verifyNewOrder​(Tour tour, java.util.List<java.lang.Long> newOrder)
      Check if the new order comform to the rules

      This method has to be used before changeOrder().

      Parameters:
      tour - the original tour
      newOrder - the order of intersections that will be applied
      Returns:
      a boolean value, false if the rules above are not respected.
      See Also:
      Tour

    • getNewPath

      public Path getNewPath​(java.lang.Long idStart, java.lang.Long idStop)
      Get the shortest path between two intersections

      A sub-method of changeOrder, it's different from shortestPathBetweenTwoIntersections because it uses the method dijkstra.

      Parameters:
      idStart - the identity of the starting intersection
      idStop - the identity of the ending intersection
      Returns:
      the object Path which is the shortest and links these two intersection
